sections.title: Interactions

requirement_evaluations.applicability_reasoning: Requirement R6 pertains to the inclusion of an infobox in the lead section of gene/protein articles. Since this section is titled 'Interactions' and is not the lead, it is not applicable.
Requirement R13 is about using infoboxes to summarize key facts at the top of the article. This section is specific to interactions and not relevant to the overall article structure.
R1 mandates the inclusion of infoboxes at the article's start. This 'Interactions' section does not fulfill this lead role and thus is not applicable.
R2 concerns the use of the Infobox GNF protein for human orthologs, which is broader than this specific interaction section.
This requirement applies to articles discussing protein families. This section specifically focuses on interaction details of ANLN.
Infobox nonhuman protein use is outside the scope of this section focused on ANLN interactions.
R5 about Pfam family infoboxes does not pertain to the interaction content of this section.
Infobox rfam is for RNA families listed in Rfam, irrelevant to this protein interaction content.
Enzyme infoboxes based on EC numbers are not applicable to the protein interaction focus of this section.
This requirement about enzyme infoboxes for unique human paralogs is not relevant to interaction specifics.
Protein family infoboxes for human paralogs in Pfam are outside the interaction details covered here.
This requirement is for managing multiple infoboxes, not relevant to a detailed interactions section.
This best practice for infobox layouts pertains to the overall article, not specifically to interaction descriptions.

sections.meta_notes: This section focuses on the detailed interactions involving ANLN in various cancer contexts and is unaffected by infobox-related requirements.
